---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

import HeroKintsugi from '~/components/widgets/v2/HeroKintsugi.astro';
import ContentKintsugi from '~/components/widgets/v2/ContentKintsugi.astro';
import FeaturesSeam from '~/components/widgets/v2/FeaturesSeam.astro';
import CTASumi from '~/components/widgets/v2/CTASumi.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Private Equity',
  description:
    "Japan's healthcare private equity market delivering compelling returns through patient capital and buy-and-hold investment strategies.",
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <HeroKintsugi
    eyebrow="§ 01 / PRIVATE EQUITY"
    titleEn="Japan's healthcare revolution through patient capital."
    titleJa="日本のヘルスケア変革を、忍耐強い資本で。"
    subtitle="Japan's private equity healthcare market has emerged as one of the world's most compelling investment destinations, delivering 3x returns on invested capital — the highest among major regions from 2010-2024."
    actions={[{ text: 'Begin a conversation', href: '/contact/' }]}
    primaryLang="en"
  />

  <ContentKintsugi
    id="overview"
    eyebrow="§ 02 / MARKET"
    title="A market at inflection."
    image={{ src: '~/assets/images/handshake.jpg', alt: 'Private Equity Partnership' }}
    intro="Japan's private equity healthcare market has emerged as one of the world's most compelling investment destinations, delivering 3x returns on invested capital — the highest among major regions from 2010-2024. With healthcare PE investments growing at 20% CAGR since 2019 and annual deal values reaching $12-15 billion, the market presents exceptional opportunities for patient capital approaches."
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Convergence of forces',
        description:
          'The convergence of demographic imperatives, digital transformation needs, and cultural shifts toward professional management creates an unprecedented environment for long-term value creation.',
      },
      {
        title: 'A buy-and-hold market',
        description:
          "Unlike the rest of Asia-Pacific where only 30% of deals are buyouts, 75% of Japanese PE transactions are full acquisitions, reflecting the market's maturity and sellers' need for complete liquidity solutions.",
      },
      {
        title: 'Patient capital in practice',
        description:
          "Extended holding periods, now averaging 5-7 years for successful partnerships, demonstrate that patient capital approaches align naturally with Japanese business culture's emphasis on long-term value creation over quarterly returns.",
      },
    ]}
  />

  <ContentKintsugi
    id="demographics"
    eyebrow="§ 03 / DEMOGRAPHICS"
    title="The demographic imperative driving sustained growth."
    isReversed
    intro="Japan faces a healthcare crisis that paradoxically creates extraordinary investment opportunities. With 30% of the population aged 65 or older and 10% over 80, the country represents the world's most aged society."
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Inexorable demand growth',
        description:
          'The hospital market is projected to reach $316.4 billion by 2029, and home healthcare is expected to double from $27.2 billion to $54.6 billion by 2033.',
      },
      {
        title: 'A succession crisis at scale',
        description:
          'Over 2.45 million Japanese SME owners are over 70, with 52% of healthcare companies reporting no identified successor. A punishing 55% inheritance tax rate makes family succession increasingly untenable, creating a pipeline of acquisition targets seeking professional management and capital partners.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Structural, not cyclical',
        description:
          "This isn't a temporary arbitrage — it's a structural shift that will define the market for the next decade.",
      },
    ]}
  />

  <FeaturesSeam
    id="sectors"
    eyebrow="§ 04 / SECTOR DYNAMICS"
    title="Distinct investment opportunities across sectors."
    subtitle="The healthcare landscape presents markedly different opportunities across sectors, each with unique characteristics and growth profiles."
    items={[
      {
        label: 'BIOTECH',
        title: 'Biotech',
        description:
          "Extraordinary government support including 6.2 billion in direct funding. Companies like PeptiDream demonstrate the sector's potential with 120+ active drug discovery programs.",
      },
      {
        label: 'AESTHETIC',
        title: 'Aesthetic medicine',
        description:
          'Growing from $18.9B in 2024 toward $30B by 2030 at 17.9% CAGR. The number of aesthetic clinics increased 43.6% from 2020-2023.',
      },
      {
        label: 'OPHTHALMOLOGY',
        title: 'Ophthalmology',
        description:
          'Combines stable reimbursable procedures with technology-driven growth potential. High capital requirements create natural barriers to entry.',
      },
      {
        label: 'DENTAL',
        title: 'Dental',
        description:
          'Proven consolidation models adapted from successful U.S. dental service organizations, navigating regulatory constraints through partnership structures.',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <ContentKintsugi
    id="transformation"
    eyebrow="§ 05 / TRANSFORMATION"
    title="Operational transformation as the cornerstone of value creation."
    intro="Japanese healthcare PE success stories reveal a consistent pattern: operational excellence trumps financial engineering. Management development proves equally critical, as PE firms introduce professional managers and performance-based compensation while respecting clinical leadership."
    items={[
      {
        title: "KKR's Kokusai Electric transformation",
        description:
          'Doubled R&D investment, increased technical headcount by 30%, recruited global talent — revenue nearly doubled and market share grew by one-third. The $2.7 billion IPO saw shares surge 32% on the first trading day.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Digital transformation gap',
        description:
          'Japan ranks 29th globally in digital competitiveness with only 42% of primary care providers using EHRs versus the 93% OECD average. The digital health market is projected to reach $90.87 billion by 2035.',
      },
      {
        title: "Unison Capital's CHCP platform",
        description:
          "Now Japan's largest private healthcare owner, demonstrating the power of technology-enabled consolidation across hospitals, pharmacies, home nursing stations, and dental clinics.",
      },
    ]}
  />

  <ContentKintsugi
    id="culture"
    eyebrow="§ 06 / CULTURE"
    title="Cultural mastery determines partnership success."
    isReversed
    intro={`The cultural dimension separates successful Japanese healthcare PE investments from expensive failures. Japanese business culture's emphasis on "wa" (harmony) and consensus-building requires fundamentally different approaches than Western markets. Successful firms invest 6-18 months in relationship building before discussing transactions.`}
    items={[
      {
        title: 'Stewardship over extraction',
        description:
          "Japanese healthcare owners prioritize business continuity and employee welfare over maximizing sale prices. They seek partners who will preserve their company's mission, protect their employees, and maintain care quality.",
      },
      {
        title: 'The Bain Capital model',
        description:
          "Bain Capital's approach to the Mitsubishi Tanabe Pharma acquisition — emphasizing enhancement rather than restructuring and retaining the company's 346-year heritage — exemplifies successful positioning.",
      },
      {
        title: 'Nemawashi as negotiation',
        description:
          'The negotiation process itself requires cultural adaptation. "Nemawashi" — behind-the-scenes consensus building — means key decisions occur before formal meetings. Direct refusals rarely occur; instead, subtle cues communicate reservations. Pressure tactics destroy trust irreparably.',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <FeaturesSeam
    id="success"
    eyebrow="§ 07 / SUCCESS STORIES"
    title="Winning strategies in practice."
    subtitle="These successes share common elements: patient capital approaches with 5-7 year holds, significant reinvestment in R&D and technology, respect for Japanese business culture while introducing global best practices, and multiple exit options. The market's ability to generate $10+ billion in combined exit value from major healthcare transactions validates the buy-and-hold thesis."
    items={[
      {
        label: 'KKR',
        title: 'KKR and PHC Holdings',
        description:
          'Seven-year journey from 2014 acquisition to 2021 IPO. Grew revenue to $2.8 billion while preserving Japanese management culture. Retained 45.77% ownership post-IPO.',
      },
      {
        label: 'ADVANTAGE',
        title: 'Advantage Partners and Nihon Chouzai',
        description:
          "94.8 billion acquisition of Japan's largest pharmaceutical chain with 760+ pharmacies. The 163.6% premium reflects confidence in long-term value creation.",
      },
      {
        label: 'J-STAR',
        title: 'J-STAR and Caregiver Japan',
        description:
          'Proprietary "Good Job!" app for integrated facility management with aggressive expansion plans across Tokyo. The "nurse\'s office in town" concept resonates with Japanese preferences for community-based care.',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <ContentKintsugi
    id="path-forward"
    eyebrow="§ 08 / PATH FORWARD"
    title="Navigating the path forward."
    intro="For PE firms targeting Japanese healthcare, success demands more than capital — it requires cultural fluency, operational expertise, and genuine long-term commitment. The messaging must emphasize stewardship over extraction, growth over cost-cutting, and partnership over control."
    items={[
      {
        title: 'An inflection point',
        description:
          'The Japanese healthcare PE market stands at an inflection point where demographic necessity, technological transformation, and cultural evolution converge. The 20% CAGR growth in healthcare PE investments reflects not speculation but fundamental value creation opportunities. With the government targeting 100 trillion yen in foreign direct investment by 2030, policy support aligns with market dynamics.',
      },
      {
        title: 'Operational excellence drives returns',
        description:
          "The firms generating 3x returns — the world's highest — aren't those applying maximum leverage or executing rapid flips. They're patient investors who understand that in Japan, the path to exceptional returns runs through operational excellence, cultural respect, and genuine long-term partnership.",
      },
      {
        title: "The developed world's last great PE opportunity",
        description:
          "For investors willing to commit the time, resources, and cultural investment necessary, Japanese healthcare offers what may be the developed world's last great PE opportunity — a massive, sophisticated market with structural growth drivers, clear value creation pathways, and an increasing openness to professional investment partners.",
      },
    ]}
  />

  <CTASumi
    id="contact"
    eyebrow="§ 09 / CONTACT"
    titleEn="Begin a long-term partnership."
    titleJa="長期的なパートナーシップを始めましょう。"
    subtitle="Discover how Deerfield Green's patient-capital approach aligns with Japanese healthcare opportunities."
    actions={[{ text: 'Begin a conversation', href: '/contact/', variant: 'primary' }]}
    primaryLang="en"
  />
</Layout>
